fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.mimetype

Class TikaBuilderDelegate<P>

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.AbstractParent<P>
      • fr.sii.ogham.core.builder.mimetype.TikaBuilderDelegate<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the parent builder (when calling AbstractParent.and() method)
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Builder<MimeTypeProvider>, TikaBuilder<P>, Parent<P>

    public class TikaBuilderDelegate<P>
extends AbstractParent<P>
implements TikaBuilder<P>
    Implementation that just delegates all operations to another builder.

    This is useful when a TikaBuilder is used for a particular parent and it must be inherited. As the parent types are not the same, you can't directly use the same reference. So this implementation wraps the original reference but as it is a new instance, it can have a different parent builder.
